// Jest Snapshot v1, https://jestjs.io/docs/snapshot-testing

exports[`calibre --help 1`] = `
"♠  calibre subcommand [options]

Commands:

  calibre site <command>       Manage your Sites.
  calibre synthetic <command>  Synthetic monitoring — manage scheduled
                               Lighthouse tests, Pages, Test Profiles,
                               Snapshots, and Pull Request Reviews.
  calibre deploy <command>     Manage deployment markers — annotate your
                               performance charts across Synthetic, CrUX, and
                               RUM data.
  calibre crux <command>       Chrome UX Report (CrUX) — real-world performance
                               data from Chrome users.
  calibre rum <command>        Real User Metrics (RUM) — field performance data
                               from your real users.
  calibre test <command>       Use the test command to run Single Page Tests:
                               public or private tests for a single Page tested
                               from a single device. This command also supports
                               viewing all Single Page Tests and retrieving
                               their artifacts.
  calibre team <command>       Use the team command to manage Teams.
  calibre token <command>      Use the token command to store or revoke a
                               Calibre API token. You can also save your token
                               with the CALIBRE_API_TOKEN environment variable.
  calibre request              Use the request command to make a request to the
                               Calibre GraphQL API.

Options:

  --help     Show help                                                 [boolean]
  --version  Show version number                                       [boolean]

Examples:

  calibre token set <token>  Store Calibre API token in
                             ~/.config/configstore/calibre.json
  calibre site list          List the sites in your Calibre account
  calibre test create <url>  Create a single page test

For more information on Calibre, see https://calibreapp.com"
`;
